                  </hi>. I am the wife of William Sharp; we live in Westmin<lb></lb>ster. Between three and four o'clock in the afternoon of the 19th of October, I saw the prisoner take the reins from the bolt of my window-shutter—I opened the door, and followed him about a hundred yards—when I came up to him, I said, "What do you do with my property?"—he said, "Your property?"—I said, "Yes," and I took these reins off his arm—he went a short distance—my husband came and gave him into custody.</p>
